@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Architecture";
}

<div class="card app-card mb-4">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h4>Architecture: MVC + 3-Layers + SignalR + Worker Service</h4>
        <p class="text-muted mb-0">This page describes the main workflows used for the PRN222 assignment demo.</p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="row g-4">
    <div class="col-lg-4">
        <div class="card app-card h-100"><div class="card-body">
            <h5>Workflow 1: Document Ingestion</h5>
            <p>PDF/DOCX/TXT/MD files are uploaded through an MVC Controller. The Service validates and parses text, the Repository saves data to SQL Server, and the Worker Service indexes documents in the background.</p>
            <code>DocumentsController -> DocumentService -> DocumentRepository -> AppDbContext -> BackgroundIndexingService</code>
        </div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-lg-4">
        <div class="card app-card h-100"><div class="card-body">
            <h5>Workflow 2: Contextual Q&A</h5>
            <p>SignalR receives the question. ChatService coordinates the RAG flow, RetrievalService fetches top chunks through the Repository, and Gemini answers with context and citations.</p>
            <code>ChatHub -> ChatService -> RetrievalService -> DocumentRepository -> GeminiClient</code>
        </div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-lg-4">
        <div class="card app-card h-100"><div class="card-body">
            <h5>Workflow 3: RBL Benchmark</h5>
            <p>EvaluationService runs PRN222 ground-truth questions, measures faithfulness, relevance, recall, and citation accuracy, then saves results through the Repository.</p>
            <code>BenchmarkController -> EvaluationService -> EvaluationRepository -> SQL Server Dashboard</code>
        </div></div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card app-card mt-4">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h5>3-Layers Mapping</h5>
        <table class="table table-sm">
            <tr><th>Presentation</th><td>Razor Views, MVC Controllers, SignalR Hub, Bootstrap UI, browser JavaScript clients.</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Business Logic</th><td>DocumentService, ChatService, EvaluationService, RetrievalService, indexing orchestration, AI clients.</td></tr>
            <tr><th>Data Access</th><td>Repositories, AppDbContext, EF Core entities, SQL Server LocalDB, migrations.</td></tr>
        </table>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="card app-card mt-4">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h5>Runtime Dependency Rule</h5>
        <p class="mb-0"><code>Controller/Hub -> Service -> Repository -> AppDbContext/EF Core -> SQL Server</code></p>
    </div>
</div>
